            "equipment": "A build sheet is provided in the photo gallery, and a partial list of notable equipment reported by the seller includes:\n- Premium Package (14-way power-adjustable and heated front seats, auto-dimming mirrors, Porsche Dynamic Light System)\n- Sport Chrono Package (dynamic engine mounts, Sport Plus driving profile, stopwatch on dashboard)\n- Power Steering Plus\n- Power sunroof\n- Ventilated front seats\n- Bose sound system\n- Front and rear ParkAssist",
            "highlights": "THIS… is a 2013 Porsche 911 Carrera Coupe, finished in black with a black interior.\n- This 911 features the desirable 7-speed manual transmission, and the odometer currently displays approximately 56,700 miles. \n- The attached `Carfax` vehicle history report shows no accidents or mileage discrepancies in this Porsche’s past. It also shows that this Carrera has been registered in California since new.\n- According to the build sheet provided in the gallery, notable factory equipment includes the Premium and Sport Chrono packages, a power sunroof, ventilated front seats, and a Bose sound system. \n- A full list of notable modifications reported by the seller is detailed below. Highlights include a Porsche sport exhaust system, an IPD plenum, a Sport Design ducktail spoiler, and a ZZ2 Apple CarPlay module.\n- Porsche introduced the 991-generation 911 for the 2012 model year. The model arrived as an evolution of its predecessor, the 997, and it received more powerful engines across the board and a more luxurious interior. It was longer, lower, and wider — and it relied extensively on aluminum to avoid putting on weight. Production of the 991 ended in 2019.\n- Power comes from a 3.4-liter flat-6, rated at 350 horsepower and 287 lb-ft of torque. Output is sent to the rear wheels via a 7-speed manual transmission.",
            "other_items": "- 2 keys\n- Owner's manual\n- Some service records\n- Factory rear spoiler, center console trim, side markers, and pedals",
            "seller_notes": "- Due to the IPD plenum installed on this 911, it may not pass emissions testing in some states, and a valid California smog inspection report from March 2026 is pictured in the gallery. As always, it’s the **buyer’s responsibility** to perform all due diligence regarding registering this Porsche in their respective state **prior to placing a bid.**\n- The seller states that paint protection film has been applied to the front end and rear fenders, a ceramic coating has been applied to the exterior, and the windows have been tinted.",
            "modifications": "Notable modifications reported by the seller include: \n\n**Powertrain:**\n- Porsche sport exhaust with interior button\n- IPD plenum\n- Porsche short shift kit\n\n**Exterior:**\n- 20-inch wheels\n- Suncoast Porsche Parts Sport Design ducktail spoiler\n- Porsche front lip spoiler\n- Porsche clear side markers\n- Custom exterior stripes\n- Gold rear badges\n\n**Interior:**\n- ZZ2 Apple CarPlay module\n- Rennline sport pedals\n- Amaranth Red-finished console and dashboard trim\n- Porsche seat belts in red and black\n- Pre-wired for Escort radar detector",
            "ownership_history": "The seller reports that they purchased this 911 in September 2023 and have added approximately 7,900 miles since.",
